 <title>Hiromi:  The Trio Project</title>
 <link>http://jazz.to/artist/hiromi-trio-project</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-web field-type-link-field field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hiromimusic.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.hiromimusic.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-photo field-type-image field-label-hidden field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://jazz.to/sites/default/files/Hiromi2.jpg&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;body field&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Known for her technique and high-energy performances, this Japanese-born pianist pushes musicianship to unprecedented levels of complexity and sophistication. An utterly original improviser and composer who turns each piece into a thrilling ride, Hiromi is one of jazz piano’s most brazenly virtuosic players capable of playing stride with blinding speed and deadly accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthony Jackson - bass&lt;br /&gt;
Simon Phillips - drums &lt;/p&gt;
